==Cretaceous==

another spelling of [[Cretaceous]].

===Uses and pronounciation===

Pronunciation: kri-'tA-sh&s

Function: adjective

===Origin===

Etymology: [[Latin]] cretaceus about/of/resembling chalk, from creta: [[chalk]].

===Definition===

A [[time]] of, relating to, or being the last [[period]] of the [[Mesozoic]] era [[characterized]] by continued dominance of [[reptiles]], emergent dominance of [[angiosperm]]s, [[diversification]] of [[mammals]], and the [[extinction]] of many types of [[organism]]s at the close of the period; also : of, relating to, or being the corresponding system of [[rocks]] found and dating back to this period.

A period representing a time in the Mesozoic, (found in [[Phanerozoic]]), era from 98 million uyears ago (for the [[Upper time scale]]) to 144 million yearas ago (for the [[Lower time scale]]).